Overview


The Decano Analytical Laboratories, LLC. provides a broad range of testing and analytical services to a cannabis industry. We at the forefront of the testing services industry, building an enviable reputation. The Decano Analytical Laboratories, LLC. provides a diversified line of independent analytical services to a wide range of top-tier customers. Our diverse laboratories perform routine and specialty analytical testing for compliance, safety, certification and verification purposes.
General Accountability:
The primary purpose of this position is to prepare, analyze and evaluate samples using HPLC, LC/MS/MS and to report data for release to clients and regulatory bodies. Knowledge of computers and mathematics are required. Ability to work independently is preferred. Duties will include maintenance of instruments and development of new methods.
Responsibilities


Specific Responsibilities:


Prepare and analyze samples for LC/MS;
Responsible for meeting calibration and QA requirements;
Document activities and report results in a concise and accurate manner using LC/MS software LIMS;
Coordinate with other laboratory analysts;
Perform routine instrument maintenance procedures;
Peer review HPLC and LC/MS data;
Report data and review reported results;
Other duties as assigned.

Required Knowledge, Skills & Abilities:


Possess a general knowledge of chemistry fundamentals and the ability to perform concentration and solution calculations; ability to understand terminology and principals in order to comply with analytical methods;
Possess strong computer skills with knowledge in Excel and Microsoft Word; experience with or ability to learn industry specific software such as Agilent Masshunter and OpenLab CDS
Organized, detail oriented, and possess excellent problem solving capabilities; be able to work independently of supervision and work well with other analysts on the team;
Ability to work overtime when necessary to meet the Decano Analytical Laboratories needs.

Job Type: Full-time


Salary: $50,000.00 - $75,000.00 per year


Schedule:


8 hour shift

Ability to commute/relocate:


Los Angeles, CA 90040: Reliably commute or planning to relocate before starting work (Preferred)

Education:


Master's (Preferred)

Experience:


CGMP: 1 year (Preferred)

Work Location: One location

